IAM (Identity and Access Management)
AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) is a service that securely controls who can access AWS resources and what actions they can perform

Authentication
Authentication is the process of verifying who you are (for example, using username/password, access keys, or MFA).

Authorization
Authorization is the process of determining what actions you are allowed to perform after you are authenticated

User
An IAM User is an individual identity created in AWS with long-term credentials to access AWS services.

Group
An IAM Group is a collection of IAM users that share the same permissions.

Role
An IAM Role is a temporary identity with specific permissions that can be assumed by users, applications, or AWS services

Policy
A Policy is a JSON document that defines permissions by specifying allowed or denied actions on AWS resources.
